<p>One of many identical small mermaid statues that are found throughout the house. It is made from glazed plaster of Paris. The word 'sculptorcraft' is found along the base &ndash; it is the name a popular company that specialised in plastic and rubber molds for Plaster of Paris in the 60s. There is an array of mermaids outside in the Camel Yard, and it is clear that this mold, although in miniature, served as their anatomical inspiration.</p>